(1, 68, 'my-5-most-pinned-hairstyles-on-pinterest.jpeg', '74', 'My 5 Most Pinned Hairstyles On Pinterest', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Hey guys! I get asked a lot about my favorite ways to wear my hair so I wanted to share not only my personal favorite hairstyles &ndash; but my most pinned hairstyles too that I&rsquo;ve worn in the past. When it comes to doing my hair I feel like there are a few underlying common things that are a must have for a good hair day, VOLUME and TEXTURE!! See them all below and let me know your favorites!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"Bubble Braid\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0564.jpg\" style=\"height:1526px; width:1242px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A little bit more of an intense hairdo, but perfect if you are going to an event or a night out or just want your hair to look bomb!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"French Braids\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0570.jpg\" style=\"height:1528px; width:1233px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The trick to these french braids is pulling and separating apart the sections of the braid afterwards to give a more full effect!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"Hairdo of the day\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0569.jpg\" style=\"height:1538px; width:1242px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Low messy bun for the win.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"topknot\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0566.jpg\" style=\"height:1538px; width:1242px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Without a doubt my favorite way to wear my hair. 99.9% of the time my hair is in a messy bun!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"beach waves\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0567.jpg\" style=\"height:1527px; width:1242px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Everyday Curls!&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">What&rsquo;s your favorite way to style your hair?!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><a href=\"https://rstyle.me/+1AN23gqXNw7-SxmscfXuVA\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">&nbsp;<img src=\"https://product-images-cdn.liketoknow.it/b_lMOBC8Np.INs7oAhLCf5W5pSLp4cU01f2H1g7ex29ycalCBUysZgwrhr6xE52pQprltwoR3QyM4pHNP1v3iFIMp3mUXREcQqQOnZ.zLSWJ9Kq0R7J9Gw9pBko-?v=2&amp;max&amp;height=0&amp;width=120\" style=\"height:150px; width:150px\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://rstyle.me/+2GEsXdOW0SJ9feobMPVXng\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">&nbsp;<img src=\"https://product-images-cdn.liketoknow.it/kriy5iZ5PjusdS2vdNZKc_noQVB.Vzf4y2evD5O2GNIfLlO0IKc.XlaK3i_72a3WjP361UhVvOR7Nt.nbtnwtMl8J25Tztgz35j_bean2_sJrHm76li8OMmaD2436zjxi5YWRYWVXxqf9ZghB.ScK7w1OHGUVLil0hry2CSnJZecN6QTYbhh4zmXIxJoB70VTX.vYJErRwkq?v=2&amp;max&amp;height=0&amp;width=120\" style=\"height:150px; width:98px\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://rstyle.me/+JtMia5ngxMJ-e2MwfXkcww\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">&nbsp;<img src=\"https://product-images-cdn.liketoknow.it/be7J26HiOwEPXIHPo1GzT0ZdYt5CNwYSvSTeCSuizfUhtcMccAvMhPcvVmue_IwOez0osNfZ6hWijmDT32xiqnm4iyoqFxWlV8fRaWA6Qwdav4jfwEObQbtTo40d6Frq?v=2&amp;max&amp;height=0&amp;width=120\" style=\"height:150px; width:150px\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://rstyle.me/+ihV9E7obdgE32U4W-7NW8w\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">&nbsp;<img src=\"https://product-images-cdn.liketoknow.it/ufEyJeTGBrKiB1NKI7UHqkfw.aRHoVpSC2Q_n6cSZ9XKwzDEPHDCeky9JVjBtvZZnC_2aUGC2dDX41zna8fL7ZQVLFsAYZLmRr19JBZKh0J75yx1ta6cxlszaFOc2M.t?v=2&amp;max&amp;height=0&amp;width=120\" style=\"height:150px; width:150px\" /></a></p>\r\n', 0, 'XX, Christine', '2021-06-25 19:04:13', 0, 0),
(2, 68, 'my-3-minute-glow-routine.jpeg', '75', 'My 3 Minute Glow Routine', '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"3 step glow routine, Tula\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Photo-May-26-11-05-53-scaled-e1622240485757.jpg\" style=\"height:1813px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Summer beauty is all about the easy, fresh-faced 2 minute beauty routines. Honestly I feel like that&rsquo;s been my routine year-round lately haha but with a little bit of that summer glow, it makes anybody&rsquo;s beauty routine that much simpler. I just discovered a few products that double as skincare and makeup that are the all-stars of summer beauty so I wanted to share my quick 3 minute glow routine!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"3 step glow routine, tula\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Photo-May-19-2-30-47-PM-scaled-e1622576224938.jpg\" style=\"height:1700px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:center\">STEP 1. HYDRATE (MOISTURE CREAM) &ndash; 15% OFF WITH CODE: CHRISTINEANDREW</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The first step in any successful beauty look is moisture! This moisturizer is super light-weight and non-greasy but still is really hydrating and leaves my skin feeling so soft. The best part is its also skincare, so it also smooths fine lines and wrinkles over time the more you use it. It&rsquo;s an essential step in both your morning and nighttime skin routine. (Don&rsquo;t forget to follow with your favorite SPF in the am!)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Screen-Shot-2021-06-09-at-4.25.26-PM.png\" style=\"height:1534px; width:968px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:center\">2. PRIME &ndash; FILTER PRIMER &ndash; 15% OFF WITH CODE: CHRISTINEANDREW</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">My second step is this filter primer &ndash; technically it&rsquo;s a primer so it leaves the prettiest finish but you can also get it in a pretty tint so it doubles as makeup to give you a gorgeous, glowy finish. Once you apply and start to blend, it matches your unique skin-tone perfectly! It comes in multiple tints (I&rsquo;m wearing the shade sunrise). And even better is that it&rsquo;s actually good for your skin and won&rsquo;t clog your pores like other primers. I&rsquo;m obsessed obsessed obsessed. I&rsquo;ve gotten tons of my friends hooked already!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"3 step glow routine, tula\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Photo-May-19-2-22-10-PM-scaled-e1622576284100.jpg\" style=\"height:1701px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"3 step glow routine, tula\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Photo-May-26-11-05-44-e1622576257234.jpg\" style=\"height:1813px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"3 step glow routine, tula\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Photo-May-26-11-06-01-scaled-e1622576297391.jpg\" style=\"height:1813px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:center\">3. HIGHLIGHT- ROSE GLOW BALM STICK &ndash; 15% OFF WITH CODE: CHRISTINEANDREW</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Last and final step to achieve this natural dewy look is this rose glow balm stick. It&rsquo;s actually an eye balm (best way to fake a good night&rsquo;s sleep when you need it the most!) but it has the prettiest consistency so I also apply the balm where I would typically conceal and highlight &ndash; my forehead, tip of my nose, above my upper lip, and a little on my chin. You can also reapply your glow throughout the day with the stick applicator &ndash; it&rsquo;s the perfect pick-me-up! This one is a best-seller and I absolutely love it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"summer beauty routine\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/ED9E504F-0006-4B32-BCB6-BD86A7A62532-e1623269902657.jpg\" style=\"height:1757px; width:1283px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Usually I&rsquo;ll just finish with some brow-gel and curling my lashes and I&rsquo;m good to go. Linking more of my favorite summer beauty products below!</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><a href=\"https://rstyle.me/+cX-7PAOHIU7QhPlBPWIWmA\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">&nbsp;<img src=\"https://product-images-cdn.liketoknow.it/CQvcnDgqCas0RbkEAd.uLQ2_19M1OgMcCnMxMzh3y7.YJ2M7csWZiNeCBV4SVcjHrNR_gF6TDCCkN8Fq4X4f65fHz3YrDn3DLye_vbJvUFRROnYlmBltSBs0RcgKfcfJw8BXSO6KiuyXO1yPOoXh23.haPFm6fkBM6p6nvpOFCFzg6pA81l7.A--?v=2&amp;max&amp;height=0&amp;width=120\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://rstyle.me/+muK90cfSOEmKfCV__bsonQ\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">&nbsp;<img src=\"https://product-images-cdn.liketoknow.it/rT3JD4wFzwFg3GkN3H.TY7GMActvfWYsi61mu0rD3gkq5C62R2u7.jj.wYYmeQ1hAwME5CdwAejxK3X_tLWSymOZt0FJ26dgglplQ4tLcZXi6E03.TPq1YqrNluaI7DWwlrRG82GC4EC_iLWvcKq8BdSJCyo4OJ_?v=2&amp;max&amp;height=0&amp;width=120\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://rstyle.me/+wa8OvZnSl21Z23KHi8i3YA\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">&nbsp;<img src=\"https://product-images-cdn.liketoknow.it/c44Lgw1lO04RtfsddD6lycKedbCSPPBESDlDVt38WDq56._W7StEA5GmN39sd3v4ot23kKT2ERkCOFkNuVWuboPAWHPmxNcGOvMzZGJMBcMl8KGtlq2xp7APPJsDLfobcaTxdOLIW9ldIQXn3CauzQmh59Cq0ghdOxiJLhrDebppaQ--?v=2&amp;max&amp;height=0&amp;width=120\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h4>&nbsp;</h4>\r\n', 0, 'XX, Christine', '2021-06-25 19:01:44', 0, 0),
(3, 68, 'my-favorite-skincare-gift-sets-on-sale.jpeg', '76', 'My Favorite Skincare Gift Sets On Sale', '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"cute christmas presents\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Photo-Nov-25-4-35-29-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1813px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"skincare everybody loves\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Photo-Nov-25-4-40-05-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1813px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"christine andrew christmas gifts\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Photo-Nov-25-4-34-08-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1814px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"kiehls gifts\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Photo-Nov-25-4-36-53-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1813px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">This set just went on sale! It has my two favorite Kiehl&rsquo;s skincare favorites and with the discount your basically getting 50% off retail!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"homebody sweatshirt\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Photo-Nov-25-4-42-22-PM-e1606754309180.jpg\" style=\"height:1813px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Just got this homebody sweatshirt last week and feel like it sums up 2020. I love it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"skincare favorites for mom\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Screen-Shot-2020-11-27-at-5.56.13-PM-e1606517894168.png\" style=\"height:743px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">One of my favorite skincare brands is running a sale on some of their best selling items/gift sets! So I had to share because these RARELY go on sale! If you ask anyone their favorite Kiehl&rsquo;s product, chances are they will have an answer haha. I have two go to&rsquo;s that I have been using for years, but wanted to share some of my fams favorites too! My makeup artist Marissa, got me hooked on the Ultra Cream, she always puts in on my face before she starts my makeup and the Midnight Revocery Oil is sooo good! (more below).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"best skincare picks\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Screen-Shot-2020-11-27-at-5.56.30-PM-e1606517934648.png\" style=\"height:612px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">I&rsquo;m obsessed with the heavy-hitting skincare products like serums and all things anti-aging, so my pick is this cult-favorite: their Midnight Recovery Concentrate. It has over 1k reviews and 4.5+ stars so I know I&rsquo;m not the only one who loves it. You put it on at night and wake up feeling like you just had a facial &ndash; it has lavender, squalane, and primrose so it also smells amaaaazing. It also lasts forever since a tiny pump goes a long way. You can also get it in a holiday kit for 25% off with the matching cleansing oil, the Ultra Facial Cream (mentioned above) and more. Let me know what you guys think of it! I also just got this energizing face mask after hearing rave reviews. It was my first time using tumeric in skincare (at least that I can remember haha). Great for a brightening mask!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"lip balm favorites for kids\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Screen-Shot-2020-11-27-at-5.56.20-PM-e1606517905185.png\" style=\"height:819px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Winter is always so hard on the skin, and the kids are washing their hands 100x times a day, it&rsquo;s a whole new level of dry right now. So I always make sure Beckam has 3 things in his backpack: hand sanitizer, hand lotion, and lip balm. The kids love the Kiehl&rsquo;s mint flavor and it&rsquo;s full of Vitamin E to keep your lips protected from the cold weather. Nordstrom has this cute holiday set right nowthat has three full size lip balms (one for Mara, Wes, and Beckam Great stocking stuffers if you can wait that long but also just a good winter essential for everyone.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"skincare favorites for mom\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Screen-Shot-2020-11-27-at-5.56.13-PM-e1606517894168.png\" style=\"height:743px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">My mom&rsquo;s favorite Kiehl&rsquo;s product is their hand salve. It has almost 500 reviews on Nordstrom alone and almost 5 stars. Definitely one of their holy grail products, so if you haven&rsquo;t tried it yet, you have to! They also have it in a little holiday set with a lavender and grapefruit sent. These would also be great neighbor/coworker gifts. They smell so good and are super rich and creamy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"skincare makeup artists love\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Screen-Shot-2020-11-27-at-5.56.39-PM-e1606517943843.png\" style=\"height:638px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">My makeup artist&rsquo;s first step when she does my makeup, without fail, is to apply Kiehl&rsquo;s Ultra Facial Cream. The best start to a good makeup look is good skin and this Kiehl&rsquo;s moisturizer is her favorite &ndash; it&rsquo;s hydrating for 24 hours and super lightweight so it makes for the best base. Nordstrom has it in this cute holiday kit (+ their best-selling avocado eye treatment) for 25% off right now or there&rsquo;s this trial-sized starter kit under $20.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">There are so many other cute Kiehl&rsquo;s holiday sets right now (and a bunch on sale for Cyber Monday!) Here are a few more of their cute sets that anyone and everyone will love.</p>\r\n', 0, 'XX, Christine', '2021-06-25 19:00:32', 0, 0),
(4, 68, '7-steps-to-get-professional-facial-results-at-home.jpeg', '77', '7 Steps to Get Professional Facial Results At Home', '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"christine andrew\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Photo-Jan-13-11-05-01-PM-1-scaled.jpg\" style=\"height:1700px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">DIY facial night!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"at-home facial nuace\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Photo-Jan-13-11-11-45-PM-scaled.jpg\" style=\"height:1700px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"how to use the nuface\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Photo-Jan-14-12-18-09-PM-scaled.jpg\" style=\"height:1813px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"microcurrent facial at home\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Photo-Jan-14-12-06-28-PM-scaled.jpg\" style=\"height:1813px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Photo-Jan-14-12-21-47-PM-scaled.jpg\" style=\"height:1813px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">Someone woke up during my spa time and wanted to cuddle!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"at-home facial\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Photo-Jan-13-11-09-41-PM-scaled.jpg\" style=\"height:1700px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pre-pandemic and pre-Ollie I was religious about going to get my facials. I would get a hydrafacial once a month, but now I think I&rsquo;ve had 2 facials since last March. Tried a vampire facial for the first time last week!&nbsp;&nbsp;Will be sharing all my thoughts soon&nbsp;&nbsp;I&rsquo;ll always love the spa experience but I know a lot of places still aren&rsquo;t open, or have limited availability if they are, so until you can get in for your next (or even first!) professional facial, bring the spa to YOUR HOME. Skincare is about consistency! So even if you are getting in for your facial take the time to pamper yourself at home too! So get cozy, and take a step into my spa routine at home&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"everything you need for home facial\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Untitled-1-scaled.jpg\" style=\"height:2172px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>PREP &amp; SET UP:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The first step to fake a luxury facial at home is to add a little luxury to the set up. Burn a luxe candle (obsessed with this scent, I&rsquo;ve posted about it a lot but I just can&rsquo;t get enough!), put on a Terry headband, your favorite pjs, wrap up in a robe, and find a relaxing playlist. (I usually take a bath or a hot shower before I start my spa day so I feel fresh and clean &ndash; it sets the tone )</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>CLEANSE:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">First and foremost, make sure you remove any and all makeup or excess dirt and oils. I&rsquo;ve been using these cotton pads for years and they are a favorite for removing makeup. Then you&rsquo;ll want to do a double cleanse with a good face wash and cloth. I&rsquo;m about to run out of this face wash and already I&rsquo;m reordering because I don&rsquo;t want to miss a day without it &ndash; it&rsquo;s that good. It&rsquo;s really gentle but also leaves my skin feeling refreshed and more radiant. If you don&rsquo;t have a face wash you&rsquo;re crazy about, try this one and let me know if you agree! It&rsquo;s also important to use something to use a wash cloth, muslin cloth, or cleansing device to help exfoliate (just ordered this one &ndash; love that it&rsquo;s deep cleansing and massaging! This one is specifically for sensitive skin.) Once you start doing the double cleanse and add a cloth or cleansing device, you&rsquo;ll realize what a difference it makes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>STEAM:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Almost all facials start with a facial steam. It&rsquo;s the best way to ensure a deep cleanse but also promotes circulation, collagen and elastin, but most importantly helps your skin absorb skincare products. I actually didn&rsquo;t know until I started researching but it&rsquo;s also super hydrating. (Not to mention so relaxing!) There are tons of at-home facial steamer options available but especially with your skin, you don&rsquo;t want to take chances so make sure you get one with great reviews like this one. This is a top seller and super easy to use and heats up fast.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>EXFOLIATE:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">There are tons of options when it comes to exfoliating. If you&rsquo;re in the mood for a face-scrub, I love this one. I saw Victoria Beckam post about it a year or so ago and immediately added it to my cart haha. For something less abrasive, you&rsquo;ll want a product with AHAs and BHAs &ndash; this one is a super quick and convenient and a cult-favorite.. Either way, keep it somewhat simple &ndash; the last thing you want to do is over-exfoliate!</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>MICROCURRENT:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Hailey Bieber is my favorite celebrity &ndash; all her beauty and fashion fits are flawless! So a year or so ago when I saw her try the microcurrent facial I was dying to try it. My next trip to NYC I booked it. I loved the immediate results but you actually need to do it regularly to see the best long lasting results. This NuFace trinity device is the next best thing if you can&rsquo;t fly to NYC or LA for a microcurrent facial every week (which really nobody can right haha). Honestly you won&rsquo;t believe before and after pictures! It makes me want to be super religious about it because it&rsquo;s the only way you&rsquo;ll see lasting results. It tones facial muscles and improves contour and skin tone while also reducing fine lines and wrinkles. You can also get the basic model here, but the Trinity comes with a lip and eye attachment to target those smaller areas. It&rsquo;s really simple to use and takes just a few minutes every day, so it&rsquo;s easy to get in the habit of it. They say even for 5 minutes for 30-60 days you will see results. I can&rsquo;t wait to start seeing some results as I keep using it!</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>MASK:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">One of my favorite parts of a facial is the mask. You can just sit, relax, and maybe even get a cat nap in while your skin is soaking up some TLC. These are a splurge but have amaaazing reviews online &ndash; will definitely be trying ASAP! I also love these eye masks &ndash; I think the eye area makes the biggest difference so if you don&rsquo;t have time for a full mask, stick these on while you go about the rest of your day. This is an overnight sleep mask that just launched at Nordstrom but has amazing reviews!</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>MOISTURIZE:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Last but not least, a few skincare staples. After your mask you will want to moisturize.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">If it&rsquo;s during the day make sure you add a SPF of 30 or higher since your skin will be extra sensitive and susceptible to sun damage. I also love a good eye cream and lip treatment after a mask. I&rsquo;m still on the hunt for an eye cream that I love but this one has a lot of good reviews and my friends always post about it, so just added to cart to try.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>MIST:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">This is another VB favorite I bought asap after I saw she loved and I am obsessed. My favorite part of the end of my at home facials is a refreshing elixir mist.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>KEEP IT COLD:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">And if you&rsquo;re in the habit of at-home facials, you&rsquo;ve probably already pulled the trigger on the beauty fridges. Not only are they so cute and extend the shelf life of some skincare products (nothing beats a cold eye cream), they also help with swelling and redness.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Have you guys tried an at-home facial? What&rsquo;s your secret ingredient?</p>\r\n', 0, 'XX, Christine', '2021-06-25 18:58:47', 0, 0),
(5, 69, 'top-9-black-friday-sales-to-shop-first.jpeg', '78', 'Top 9 Black Friday Sales to Shop First', '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/IMG_0045.jpeg\" style=\"height:1948px; width:1242px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/IMG_0046.jpeg\" style=\"height:2268px; width:1242px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">I hope you guys had a happy Thanksgiving! It was so nice to be able to relax with the fam, totally disconnect from work, and just hang with the fam! I saw some of my favorite retailers launch their sales yesterday and was tempted to shop, but honestly I was totally soaking in the holiday and figured it could wait until today.&nbsp;So here are some of my favorite Black Friday sales going on right now and some selects from each! (I&rsquo;ll also be sharing some small businesses tomorrow for Small Business Saturday so check back in!) A ton of pieces from my Ultimate Gift Guide are on sale too, so don&rsquo;t miss that post!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/hm-scaled.jpg\" style=\"height:2560px; width:1285px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">I&rsquo;ve been on the biggest H&amp;M kick. I love their collection right now and also the styling is on point! So many great outfit ideas and even better since it&rsquo;s all at such accessible price points. Everything is 30% off right now &ndash; sherpa jackets are my favorite right now but also so hard to get your hands on. They just launched this one&nbsp;that comes in two colors and they are both so good and under $50. Also love&nbsp;<a href=\"https://bit.ly/33mZMuh\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">t</a>his pullover&nbsp;&ndash; the black zip detail is</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/anthro-1-scaled.jpg\" style=\"height:2560px; width:1192px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Black Friday is the best time to pull the trigger on those big investment items you&rsquo;ve been putting off. Right now Anthropologie&nbsp;is 30% off site-wide. I have this mirror and it was one of my favorite purchases for the house &ndash; I had been wanting to order it for forever and was so happy with it! So if you&rsquo;ve been waiting for the right time to order, this is it. They also have the prettiest home and furniture pieces &ndash; lighting especially. How pretty is this sconce!</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/kohls.jpg\" style=\"height:2532px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Kohl&rsquo;s constantly has great sales but right now they are adding an extra 15% off on top of regular sale price &ndash; like these slipper&nbsp;for under $10! I bought them full price months ago and LOVE them! So cozy and soft &ndash; such a great gift and a steal right now! They also have so many of our families favorite brands like Nike, Adidas, Levi&#39;s, Vans,&nbsp;etc&hellip; so definitely stock up while it&rsquo;s on such major sale right now!</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong><img alt=\"BLACK FRIDAY\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/lululemon.jpg\" style=\"height:1954px; width:1360px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Lululemon rarely has sales (like almost never haha) but Black Friday is one of the exceptions. They have lots of pieces included in the sale, but the sizes will go quick. This pair&nbsp;is super comfortable (and has pockets &ndash; a must!). Also obsessed with all their sports bras!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"mango black friday\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/mango.jpg\" style=\"height:2388px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">I ordered a bunch of Mango&nbsp;pieces this week and can&rsquo;t get wait to get my hands on them! They have such timeless pieces and great quality &ndash; love all their colors schemes right now!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Insta2b.jpg\" style=\"height:1630px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">My faaaavorite jewelry brand! I think they only do sales on Black Friday so don&rsquo;t miss out. The majority of the jewelry I own is all from them and it&rsquo;s such high quality.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"nordstrom black friday\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/nordstrom.jpg\" style=\"height:2266px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nordstrom has tons of pieces included in their Black Friday sale right now and one of the best places to shop for the whole family + beauty finds. These boots&nbsp;are 50% off!! Love the croc texture and the color &ndash; so good but sizes are going quick! Topshop jeans are always a steal, even full-priced but these&nbsp;are under $40 right now! Love the distressing and fit! If you haven&rsquo;t tried these bras yet, now it the perfect chance while they are 20% &ndash; soooo comfortable. Also this fleece coat&nbsp;&nbsp;would be so cute this winter with leggings and these boots!</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/shopbop-scaled.jpg\" style=\"height:2560px; width:1068px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"zulily sale\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Screenshot-2020-11-23-at-10.37.32-PM-scaled-e1606495635386.jpeg\" style=\"height:1900px; width:1125px\" /></h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">I didn&rsquo;t know much about Zulily until I started working with them this year, but they have sooooo much product and at amazing prices. You have to sign up for an account to view everything so don&rsquo;t let that stop you because they have some great stuff. There&rsquo;s sooo much of it though so I&rsquo;m working on putting together a gift guide with some of my favorites. These coats are my favorite find so far! Soooo comfy and warm and I love the zipper details</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Below are some more of my favorite finds on sale for Black Friday!</p>\r\n', 0, 'XX, Christine', '2021-06-25 18:56:19', 0, 0),
(6, 69, 'last-minute-holiday-prep-hacks-.jpeg', '79', 'Last Minute Holiday Prep Hacks!', '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Photo-Dec-15-3-11-29-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1813px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"Christine Andrew\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Photo-Dec-15-3-10-48-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1813px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nothing like wrapping presents to get you into the holiday prep spirit haha.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"christine andrew holidays\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Photo-Dec-15-3-18-01-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1700px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"kids christmas gift ideas\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Photo-Dec-15-3-29-01-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1813px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"best holiday prep hacks\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Photo-Dec-15-3-34-18-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1077px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"holiday prep hacks\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Photo-Dec-15-3-32-17-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1813px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"kohls holiday style\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Photo-Dec-15-15-46-23.jpg\" style=\"height:1813px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">Switched into these joggers&nbsp;and had to share! So soft!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"holiday gift wrap\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Photo-Dec-16-12-12-39.jpg\" style=\"height:1777px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"holiday prep\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Photo-Dec-16-12-12-54.jpg\" style=\"height:1639px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">T minus 9 days to Christmas! There&rsquo;s so much going on around this time of year that it&rsquo;s easy for things to get lost in the shuffle. I love the gift-wrapping, helping kids pick out presents for their siblings, and wandering through store aisles even after I think I&rsquo;m done shopping and seeing things that remind me of someone and grabbing it just because.&nbsp;But I know it can also feel chaotic so I wanted to share some last minute holiday prep ideas, from last minute Christmas gifts to wrapping ideas, and more.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:center\">WRAPPING HACKS:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">I have a love hate relationship with gift wrapping. I want to make the present pretty but about 5 presents into it at 11pm on Christmas Eve Cody is like why are you taking 15 minutes on one present hahah. So I&rsquo;ve settled on doing one &ldquo;special&rdquo; gift for each kid I add little trinkets too and make super pretty. I don&rsquo;t know if you guys have noticed but a lot of stores are super picked over right now as far as their wrapping selections but I found the prettiest wrapping papers in store at Kohl&rsquo;s! I also love adding ribbons and other trinkets to the outside of the wrapped gifts. Sometimes I&rsquo;ll just add some greenery, but for their 1 special gift I like to add something a little extra like a cute ornament (love this polar bear one!), candy, or a small holiday-packaged gift set (these were perfect with Mara&rsquo;s pink wrapping paper!) just to make it feel special</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Also if you ever cut your wrapping paper just a bit too short for your box, instead of scrapping it and starting over, turn your box diagonal! You&rsquo;ll fold the pieces in at an angle so they cover your box, but you end up using less wrapping paper that way and it looks just as cute! You can see the hack on my IGTV from my live with Kohl&rsquo;s today here.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"last minute gifts\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/kohlscollage.jpg\" style=\"height:1992px; width:1242px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:center\">LAST MINUTE GIFT IDEAS:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Shipping is at an all time high this year and shipping times are delayed. So go in store or do online order pick up. Not only is it a great source of inspiration if you need new ideas, you also avoid the delay of shipping times. Here are some great gift ideas found at Kohl&rsquo;s:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">For him: Guys can sometimes feel like the hardest so shop for but in some ways they are also the easiest. Think practical and function. I got Cody this electric toothbrush (it comes in multiple colors but I love the chic all black)&nbsp;and also a new pair of gloves&nbsp;(the tech touch is a must so they can still use their phone). For the coffee-connoisseurs, he will love this milk frother&nbsp;to make his homemade lattes a little more special. I also got Cody this trio cup holder&nbsp;that turns one cup holder into three &ndash; it was an in-store find and something I never would have thought of but I know he will end up using it all the time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">For her: You can never go wrong with a cozy pair of slippers&nbsp;or a comfy throw blanket. Also love the idea of cute beauty gift sets&nbsp;&ndash; it&rsquo;s the best time of the year to find already cute, pre-packaged sets&nbsp;and they are usually at a better price point than if you were to purchase separately. I also love getting kitchen stuff! Obsessed with this copper tea kettle&nbsp; &ndash; it makes for the prettiest kitchen accent!</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">For kids: I have a feeling this Robot Combat set&nbsp;will be my kids favorite this year. It gets amazing reviews and is one of the hot ticket items this year. It&rsquo;s remote-controlled and I love that it&rsquo;s something they can do together! My kids also love doing crafts together (another gift to spend more family time together&nbsp;&nbsp;so I love this art box and this rainbow craft kit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">For teens: The Instax mini cameras&nbsp;are always a huge hit with teens and come in so many cute colors! Such a fun way for them to be able to capture memories. Another winner is the old-school mini arcade games &ndash; how cute is this Mis. Pac-man&nbsp;one? Also love the idea of a bluetooth speaker&nbsp;as they start to get to that stage instawhere they want to be listening to music and hanging out in their rooms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">There&rsquo;s seriously so much great holiday inspo in-store and it&rsquo;s a great way to get your creative juices flowing and brainstorm if you are stuck on the last few people on your list. Kohl&rsquo;s has tons of amazing in-store options or also super convenient and easy curb-side pick up so you can avoid shipping altogether. Below are a few more cute last minute holiday prep ideas! You can also get 15-20% off at Kohl&rsquo;s right now with code: YOUSAVE to make holiday prep even easier!</p>\r\n', 0, 'XX, Christine', '2021-06-25 18:55:38', 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `blogs` (`blog_id`, `cat_id`, `blog_image`, `blog_topic`, `blog_title`, `blog_content`, `blog_comments`, `blog_authors`, `blog_post`, `blog_view`, `blog_like`) VALUES
(7, 70, 'bonus-mom-part-1.jpeg', '82', 'Bonus mom part 1', '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/IMG_4499-1-1024x1820.jpg\" style=\"height:1209px; width:680px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"advice on being a bonus mom\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/IMG_4043-1024x768.jpg\" style=\"height:510px; width:680px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">I&rsquo;m so excited to start this series! Questions about being a stepmom/bonus mom and our blended family are always my most asked questions. So I wanted to start a series about blended families, being a bonus mom, and growing up with divorced parents.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">My parents divorced when I was little, 4 or 5. I primarily lived with my dad (in Washington state) and then would go spend half the summer with my mom (in Virginia). My dad got remarried when I was 5 or 6, and my step mom became a big part of my life too. Very grateful for all of my parents, but I think going through a split family dynamic growing up helped me understand a few things as a step/bonus mom and brought some perspective to certain things I see my bonus kids go through now.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Before I start, I want to preface this by saying, no two situations are exactly the same, but being a parent (bonus mom or regular mom) is always easier when you have a community, friends, or family to rely on or talk to. I feel like you guys are all my besties so I hope this series can maybe help anyone navigating being a bonus mom, or dating someone with kids. And in case you don&rsquo;t follow me on &nbsp;instagram and are wondering where these questions below came from- I did a Q&amp;A and had you submit all your blended fam/bonus mom questions. I compiled the most asked questions and will be breaking them into different posts (And it will also give you guys time to ask questions in comments below that I can include in my future posts.)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">So here we go&hellip;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:center\">THE BEGINNING</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><em>Q. How long have you and Cody been together and&nbsp;</em><em>where&nbsp;</em><em>did you meet?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A. We&rsquo;ve been married for 10 years this fall! We met selling alarm systems door to door in South Carolina and Texas. We both sold&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Q.&nbsp;<em>How many babies did you birth? Which ones are your step kids?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A. The oldest two, Mara and Wes are my bonus babies (Cody was married before and had Mara and Wes with his ex-wife). Beckam and Ollie I birthed, and are my biological children.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"Christine Andrew family step mom\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-10.47.23-AM.jpeg\" style=\"height:816px; width:680px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><em>Q. Was it hard for you to date Cody initially because he had two babies?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A. I actually had a serious boyfriend in college who had kids. I knew I always wanted to have a big family and I had a great example of a stepmom/bonus mom growing up, so dating a guy with kids was never a big deal for me. I know this is not always the case, a lot of you have &nbsp;messaged me saying it&rsquo;s been a hard transition dating someone with kids, but the biggest piece of advice I can give you is give it time. Our situation wasn&rsquo;t easy at first. The divorce was hard on a lot of people and things took time. &nbsp;Eventually you&rsquo;ll develop a structure, find what works for you and your family, and get into the swing of things. I would also say for the kids&rsquo; sake, unless you really see yourself with this person for a long time, I wouldn&rsquo;t rush to meet the kids if you don&rsquo;t see it being long term.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"bonus mom Q&amp;A\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/img_1697.jpeg\" style=\"height:510px; width:680px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Q.&nbsp;<em>How do you handle emotions about his past/firsts? (Jealousy, resentment, sadness).</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A. For the most part, I didn&rsquo;t really think about knowing he had done things without me or experienced things first before me. &nbsp;It wasn&rsquo;t something I consciously thought about or dwelt on,&nbsp; but there were a few random moments when it hit me&hellip;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Right after I had Beckam there was a moment I was like &lsquo;Oh, he&rsquo;s already done this&rsquo;. He had gone through and experienced a lot of the first time parent things already.. I thought to myself I could be mad or jealous he wasn&rsquo;t going through it the first time with me or I could look for the positive like &lsquo;hey he will know what to do maybe in times I won&rsquo;t&rsquo;.&nbsp;This is a life lesson I&rsquo;ve learned over the years in general, you always have a choice on your mindset to focus on positive or the negative.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"Cody Andrew kids\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/IMG_3489-1024x1365.jpg\" style=\"height:907px; width:680px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">I do remember asking him when we were home one of the first couple days with Beckam, &ldquo;Does it feel any different this time around?&rdquo; I am always pretty open with how I feel. I wear my emotions on my sleeve. I think communication is even more important with blended families, because it&rsquo;s really easy to let emotions/feelings bottle up inside and it super important to have a lot of communication to understand and support each other.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The other time I can really remember was when I wanted to go to Paris for the first time. Cody had gone with his ex-wife and didn&rsquo;t love all the touristy things (he&rsquo;s not big on museums or seeing all the sites) so when we first got married he wasn&rsquo;t super anxious to go back and I hadn&rsquo;t been to Europe in years, and didn&rsquo;t want my first time being in a city I had been dyiiiing to go to to be thinking about him and his ex wife. I honestly don&rsquo;t know why that event stood out to me, but it&rsquo;s the one thing I didn&rsquo;t want to repeat. Instead of going with Cody, I decided to take Beckam.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"christine and beckam Andrew\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/5F6C15AF-3745-4A5A-804D-FB11D69CB962-e1623080303249.jpeg\" style=\"height:1019px; width:680px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">He was 6 months old and my friend Amber (you guys probably know her &ndash; Dae/Barefoot Blonde) and I took our babies with our friend Jaci and it was such an amazing trip! It&rsquo;s honestly one of my favorite memories with Beckam to this day. And now we&rsquo;ve been back to Paris as a family a couples times and I love it. It&rsquo;s one of my favorite family spots. But for some reason that first time to a bucket list place I didn&rsquo;t want to be thinking about what he did with his ex wife</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"blended family advice\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/IMG_1062-1024x1122.jpeg\" style=\"height:745px; width:680px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"step mom Christine Andrew\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/IMG_4413-scaled-e1623082124986.jpeg\" style=\"height:907px; width:680px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">I think there&rsquo;s something about those &lsquo;firsts&rsquo;. Maybe we build them up in our head, but if there is something that is important to you, talk to your spouse or significant other. I was really up front with Cody about it and he understood. I mean I don&rsquo;t think he totally understood my emotions behind it, but he supported us going and wanted me to go have fun. On that same note, and I want to emphasize this,&nbsp;<em>you are entitled to all of your feelings</em>.&nbsp;You&rsquo;re entitled to feel jealousy at times, resentment, or sadness. But then how you handle it is on YOU. You have a decision to make: what are you going to do about it? You can just sit in your feelings and build bitterness, or you can acknowledge them and then try to grow and change. I know everyone will handle things differently &ndash; and it&rsquo;s not to say I have never felt sad, jealous or hurt, but I hope it can bring some connection and encouragement to those of you going through the same thing.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"being a bonus mom hello fashion blog\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/img_2906.jpeg\" style=\"height:832px; width:680px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Q.&nbsp;<em>Tips for dating someone with 2 kids with someone else?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A. I think my biggest advice would be to put the kids&rsquo; wellbeing first and foremost. That might not be what you&rsquo;re expecting, but instead of thinking how the kids could affect you or your relationship, think about how you could be affecting the kids. My #1 piece of advice: wait to meet the kids. Don&rsquo;t rush things and give it a little time, just out of respect for the kids. Especially if you don&rsquo;t see yourself getting really serious with their parent &ndash; it&rsquo;s not fair to them to have a new person in and out of their lives that doesn&rsquo;t intend to be in it long-term. Put yourself in their shoes.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"hello fashion blog family married kids\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/D0526502-91A4-44A2-AE91-B3B5659D6044-1024x1133.jpeg\" style=\"height:708px; width:640px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Q:&nbsp;<em>How did Cody introduce you to the kids? About to go through this &amp; I look up to your family.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A. This can vary so much depending on your situation, the kids ages, etc. I think meeting somewhere that&rsquo;s neutral territory is a great idea. Somewhere outside your space and outside their space so everyone feels comfortable. Another idea is to do some sort of activity you can do together so you all have time to warm up and conversation can flow easier and more natural. It&rsquo;s funny I had forgotten about this until you guys asked, but I met Cody and the kids at the McDonald&rsquo;s Play Place &ndash; and we got ice cream.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Q.&nbsp;<em>How soon did you meet the kids when you and Cody were dating? Did they accept you at first?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A. I met Mara and Wes 6 months after Cody and I started dating. They were honestly so young I feel like they warmed up super easy, and I love kids, and babysat and nannied a lot so I feel like overall I&rsquo;m good with kids which made it easier. I&rsquo;ve known Mara and Wes since they were toddlers so I&rsquo;ve been lucky that they&rsquo;ve mostly grown up with me in their life.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Q.&nbsp;<em>How did your family accept that Cody had kids?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A. I touched on this earlier, but I was pretty serious with the guy I dated before who had kids, so I don&rsquo;t think this was ever an issue really for my parents. I never straight out asked them though&hellip; I think their main concern was that if I married someone with kids, he was a good dad. It&rsquo;s funny, I think seeing guys as a dad helps you identify the good ones even faster.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"Cody Andrew wedding \" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/IMG_7366.jpg\" style=\"height:1020px; width:680px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"Christine Andrew step kids bonus mom\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/IMG_7367.jpg\" style=\"height:453px; width:680px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Q.&nbsp;<em>What did you do for your bonus children when you guys got married?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A. Mara was our flower girl and Wes was our ring bearer. I honestly can&rsquo;t remember if I got them a specific gift or memento for the wedding, but I&rsquo;ve seen the cutest ideas and gestures online after we got married &ndash; there are so many creative and thoughtful things you can do to make them feel special and loved! I think ages play into this on what kind of gift or sentiment to do&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>BALANCING BONUS &amp; BIO</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Q.&nbsp;<em>Do you ever feel like your own kids get put second to your bonus kids? Struggle bus here.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A. Hmm this was an interesting question&hellip; I think having limited time with my bonus kids makes me want to make sure we are making the most of that time, so I feel like Cody and I are more intentional and mindful of that time. With Beckam and Ollie, its more routine if that makes sense, but the days we have Mara and Wes we try to make sure we are wrapping up work right at 5 or earlier so we can get more quality time together, planning something fun for the weekends, etc. So it&rsquo;s not that we treat Ollie and Beckam different, but we do treat the time we have with Mara and Wes differently, if that makes sense&hellip;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The other time it feels like we do things differently is holidays, and it&rsquo;s not that I feel like our kids get put &lsquo;second&rsquo;, it&rsquo;s that we have to make some adjustments for schedules and splitting times on holidays. So that becomes the priority vs how an unblended family might celebrate. For example, we always split Christmas with Mara and Wes&rsquo; mom, so some years Beckam has to wait until the afternoon to open presents or on Easter we do the Easter egg hunt later after we get them. So not getting put second, just adjusting some traditions because we would rather have Mara and Wes with us to celebrate together as a family.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"blended family Christine Andrew \" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/View-recent-photos-1.jpeg\" style=\"height:822px; width:680px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Q.&nbsp;<em>How long were you a bonus mom before having Beckam and Ollie?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A. 3ish years I think&hellip; honestly I have the worst memory with dates, Cody is so much better at that than me&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"how to be a bonus fam\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/IMG_1722-1024x768.jpg\" style=\"height:510px; width:680px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Q.&nbsp;<em>How did you feel the change was when you had B?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A. There were two big changes for me &ndash; #1) Before I had Beckam, Mother&rsquo;s Day sucked. Of course Mara and Wes are going to spend Mother&rsquo;s Day with their mom, and I would never want or expect them to be with me instead of their mom on that day. But as a bonus mom you spend a lot of time loving and nurturing and building a bond with your bonus babies, so selfishly I wanted to celebrate with them too. I was/am so grateful for them and for the love they have brought into my life, so it was hard not getting to be with them on that day. Cody was always thoughtful and did something before Mother&rsquo;s Day with all of us to celebrate being a bonus mom, but it&rsquo;s still a reminder on the day of when so many people were celebrating that you just wish you could hug your bonus babies. Once I had Beckam and Ollie, Mother&rsquo;s Day changed for me and took some of that away. I still miss seeing Mara and Wes so much on that day, but it&rsquo;s nice I get to be with the other kids.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"mara Andrew Weston Andrew beckam Andrew ollie cruz Andrew\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/IMG_3982-2-scaled-e1623084121374.jpg\" style=\"height:850px; width:680px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;#2) Having Beckam and Ollie brought so much perspective to how it might feel on the other side of the equation, things that until you have kids of your own probably won&rsquo;t make sense. Like in some ways I wonder if I was too involved before&hellip; some of this is hard to put into words, but it brought perspective to not feeling like I had to be a part of as many decisions with Mara and Wes, and to give their mom space like at school functions. Example&hellip; before I had Beckam and Ollie I signed up to help in Mara and Wes&rsquo; classes and volunteered for things, and yes I&rsquo;m so glad I did that, but I also realized maybe that&rsquo;s something their mom just wants to do&hellip;as I&rsquo;m writing this I realize I probably should have just asked her instead of assuming either way. I also felt like it brought perspective to her side of splitting time&hellip; Splitting time sucks for both parents 100%, but before I had my own kids, I always sided with Cody, and then once I had Beckam and Ollie I imagined having to share so much time with Beckam and Ollie with another woman/family, not seeing every milestone, splitting holidays, all of that sucks&hellip;&nbsp;of course you want your kids to be loved by as many people as possible, but it made me understand her point of view a little more in some ways, that until you have your own kids you don&rsquo;t really understand as a bonus mom.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"blended family advice\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/IMG_6069-1024x1024.jpg\" style=\"height:640px; width:640px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Q.&nbsp;<em>How did you guys decide on &ldquo;ours&rdquo; babies. My bf is 10 years older and 3 kids &ndash; I&rsquo;m worries he&rsquo;s done. LOL</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A. This is a conversation I would FOR SURE have before you get married. I thought Cody and I did but he says he doesn&rsquo;t remember. He was always on board for us to have one together, but I always wanted at least 2 because I was an only child and always wished I had a sibling. Since we don&rsquo;t have Mara and Wes full time I didn&rsquo;t want one of our kids to be by themselves when Mara and Wes are gone, so I always wanted at least 2. Cody didn&rsquo;t realize that so he thought he was done after Beckam and it took me yearsssss to convince him on another. Obviously he&rsquo;s glad we did now that we have Ollie, but it&rsquo;s still an important conversation to have prior to make sure you&rsquo;re on the same page.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"bonus mom tips\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/IMG_5729-1024x1024.jpeg\" style=\"height:640px; width:640px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">Wes and Mara with baby B&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"andrew blended family\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/IMG_5756-1024x1024.jpg\" style=\"height:640px; width:640px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Q.&nbsp;<em>How did you talk to the kids about having another baby (meaning before Beckam was born?)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A. Honestly it&rsquo;s been so long ago that I don&rsquo;t remember how we told the kids, but I remember surprising everyone in our family somehow. They were really excited &ndash; both with Beckam and Ollie.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/B2E128B1-A709-4DF5-AC7D-AD43E584242B.jpeg\" style=\"height:810px; width:680px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Q.<em>&nbsp;I had a really awful step-mom experience &ndash; did you ever worry about treating the kids different?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A. I&rsquo;m so sorry &ndash; I feel like I get messages like this A LOT &nbsp;and it makes me so sad. &nbsp;I pray everyday my bonus kids feel loved when they are with us and know how much they mean to me. I&rsquo;m sure I&rsquo;ve done things wrong, but I think as a parent we always want to strive to be better, so I hope they always know how loved they are, not just them but all our kids.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/IMG_6514-scaled-e1623100852270.jpg\" style=\"height:1805px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">That wraps up part one! Some of the upcoming posts will talk about schedules, things I&rsquo;ve learned being a bonus moms, discipline/parenting my kids vs. bonus kids, how involved I am with ex-wife, etc&hellip; if you have new questions or questions about anything above drop in the comments below.</p>\r\n', 0, 'XX, Christine', '2021-06-25 19:06:02', 1, 0),
(8, 70, 'fall-baby-basics-to-mix-and-match-this-season.jpeg', '83', 'Fall Baby Basics to Mix and Match This Season', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">I have been just as excited finding cute fall pieces for Ollie as for myself (if not more excited!) so I wanted to share some recent pieces I&rsquo;m loving &ndash; also include some pink and gender neutral pieces that are great wardrobe baby basics to mix and match.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"winter baby essentials\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/4c6da962-1307-11eb-b869-0242ac110003.jpg\" style=\"height:810px; width:810px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Babies in beanies are my biggest weakness! We have this one&nbsp;in multiple colors (more color options here).&nbsp; Also I know it seems kind of early to post but their winter pieces sell out quick and they are super budget friendly (each piece is under $35) so I wanted to share asap. &nbsp;I love this padded jacket and matching&nbsp;snow pants&nbsp;&ndash; can&rsquo;t wait to watch him play in the snow this year!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"baby girl fall pieces\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/a3057536-130d-11eb-b869-0242ac110003.jpg\" style=\"height:810px; width:810px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">I&rsquo;ve always loved baby girl clothes! There are so many pretty pink and nude tons this year especially &ndash; dying over these snow pants in pink! These boots&nbsp;are also a great basic. We got them in multiple colors for Ollie including this white pair.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"fall baby basics\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/b00ff41c-0d79-11eb-b6b1-0242ac110003.jpg\" style=\"height:810px; width:810px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">This wool coat&nbsp;is one of my favorite baby layers I&rsquo;ve seen this season! It comes in 4 colors and they are all so good. I also love the knit leggings for babies &ndash; especially with cute fall booties. These leggings&nbsp;are one of the best baby basics. They are great gender neutral color combo and they also come in a pretty deep green set and a navy set. You can&rsquo;t have enough of these! So comfortable and versatile.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"fall baby basics\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/1b64b622-0d75-11eb-b6b1-0242ac110003-1.jpg\" style=\"height:810px; width:810px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Honestly, cute socks are probably the last thing I think about when it comes to baby but a pretty knit sock actually goes a long way! I love this ribbed set&nbsp;&ndash; Ollie has been living in them! I&rsquo;m also obsessed with these ribbed shirts. They comes in 3 color combos &ndash; one with pinks and another with the prettiest nudes and light blue.</p>\r\n', 0, 'XX, Christine', '2021-06-25 18:54:18', 0, 1),
(9, 70, 'the-snoo--yay-or-nay-.jpeg', '84', 'The Snoo: Yay or Nay?', '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/IMG_3903-720x972.jpg\" style=\"height:972px; width:720px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/IMG_3863-720x972.jpg\" style=\"height:972px; width:720px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/IMG_3860-720x972.jpg\" style=\"height:972px; width:720px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/IMG_3902-720x1150.jpeg\" style=\"height:1150px; width:720px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/IMG_3900-720x1059.jpeg\" style=\"height:1059px; width:720px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Hi guys! After using the Snoo&nbsp;for the last few months, &nbsp;to give a full review on our experience, pros and cons, &nbsp;how it&rsquo;s helped, what we learned along the way, and most importantly whether I think it&rsquo;s worth the splurge. So keep reading to get my full review:</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>A rough start&hellip;</h1>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To be fully transparent, Ollie didn&rsquo;t love the Snoo right off the bat. I had heard so many raving reviews, so I was surprised that he didn&rsquo;t take to it immediately but after mentioning this on my stories, I got tons of DMs suggesting we swaddle Ollie before we put him in the sleeper sack, and that made all the difference! I had prior just been zipping him into the sleep sack and he had so much room to kick around, so once we swaddled him he loved being all cozy inside. He also has acid reflux and I found out that Snoo has risers that keep his head elevated to help with his reflux. Honestly those two changes were game changers and he loved it from then on!</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>My favorite features:</h1>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">There are sooo many amazing features of the Snoo that you can read about here, but I just wanted to focus on a few that we used the most. It&rsquo;s a smart sleeper, so it basically senses when your baby starts to cry and starts rocking. The more your baby fusses the faster it rocks and then once they settle down it weans them off the motion.&nbsp; It&rsquo;s seriously genius and helped soothe Ollie in his bassinet. It also has a built-in noise machine that automatically kicks in or adds more sounds when it senses the fussing.&nbsp; It&rsquo;s like having an extra set of hands &ndash; honestly so helpful! It can also track their sleep cycles with the app. We didn&rsquo;t use the app but all my friends swear by it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The biggest thing for me though was the safety. I don&rsquo;t know if it&rsquo;s the older I get I hear more sad stories about freak incidents, but I was extra on edge about SIDS or something happening. The Snoo is 1005 the safest sleeper on the market. It keeps your child on their back so they can&rsquo;t roll and that brought me more sleep at night knowing I didn&rsquo;t have to wake up and worry he had tolled over. (Also have to mention for my crappy half asleep nights of swaddling him, the velcro/zipper is a life saver to make up for my sloppy swaddles. ; It made it incredibly easy to get him cozy again without worrying about him wiggling out.)</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>The cons:</h1>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">It&rsquo;s not super portable. It&rsquo;s pretty heavy &ndash; but we didn&rsquo;t really need to move it from our room but it just prevented us from really moving it anywhere because of that and because it has to be plugged in so you need to stay close to an outlet.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">We also had a little trouble connecting it to our phone &ndash; they sent us a WiFi extender but I honestly just never got around to connecting it which is laziness on my part and he was ok without having the app, so I just didn&rsquo;t do it. A lot of my friends LOVE and swear by the app so maybe I&rsquo;m missing out big time but I just got lazy.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1><strong>Worth it?</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The big question&hellip; is it worth the splurge? I work from home a lot of the time, and there were a number of times I was like wow, I&rsquo;m able to do ____ because my hands are free while The Snoo rocks Ollie. Yes, that also left me feeling a little mom guilt sometimes too but it allowed me to get more done while at home which was huge for me.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The cost of the Snoo&nbsp;will obviously hit everyone&rsquo;s budgets differently, so if you are in a position to splurge on something for baby, it&rsquo;s a no brainer! (Especially if you are planning to have a few kids &ndash; it&rsquo;s something you&rsquo;ll use with every baby!) They also have a 30 day money back guarantee so if you try it and don&rsquo;t love it you can ship it back at no cost to you! I think they know once you start using it you will instantly see the value in it like we did. They also have an amazing new option that you can rent the Snoo. Honestly I think it&rsquo;s 100% worth the money whether you rent or buy. I will use it again if we have another and all my friends who have it love it too.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Have any of you guys used The Snoo&nbsp;before? I&rsquo;m curious about your experience &ndash; whether your baby took to it immediately or you figured out what worked for your baby along the way. Let me know in the comments!</p>\r\n', 0, 'XX, Christine', '2021-06-25 18:54:02', 0, 0),
(10, 71, 'summer-nights---shopping.jpeg', '100', 'Summer Nights & Shopping', '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"summer dress\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Photo-Jun-07-5-51-10-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1700px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Obsessed with&nbsp;<a href=\"https://bit.ly/3i3HhU7\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">this dress</a>! The scrunched sleeve detail is such a pretty detail but also makes it easy to transition the dress for spring and summer if you want shorter/longer sleeves and to give it more of a full, voluminous sleeve.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"hello fashion summer shopping\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Photo-Jun-07-5-46-16-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1700px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"christine andrew summer\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Photo-Jun-07-5-51-11-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1700px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Yesterday was just one of those days where even the simplest moments feel like heaven. Chalk it up to the kids being out of school or feeling like summer is finally here &ndash; either way I had such a fun time just hanging out at the mall with Beckam and Ollie! We&rsquo;re heading out of town later this week and I needed to grab a few things for our trip, so it turned into a whole evening. We ran through the fountains and Beckam collected blank gift cards. It was so fun just to be able to walk around and enjoy shopping and the boys being silly. Beckam is so much fun to hang out with right now &ndash; I&rsquo;m loving this age so much! He&rsquo;s so silly and makes me laugh all the time. Love these moments together. XX</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"doona trike christine andrew\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Photo-Jun-07-5-49-52-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1700px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">I always get so many questions on Olie&#39;s trike. It&rsquo;s a trike meets stroller and the best thing ever! Cannot recommend it enough!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"andrew kids\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Photo-Jun-07-5-47-40-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1700px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"ollie andrew summer style\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Photo-Jun-07-5-49-18-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1700px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Ollie is as obsessed with the strawberry lemonade as his mom. If you haven&rsquo;t tried the Nordstrom strawberry lemonade, it&rsquo;s sooo good!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"beckam andrew ollie andrew\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Photo-Jun-07-7-00-58-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1700px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">Beckam told me last night that he wants to be a dad when he grows up &ndash; so he wanted to push Ollie.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Photo-Jun-07-7-46-07-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1813px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">Almost didn&rsquo;t see him there.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Photo-Jun-07-5-57-13-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1700px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Love this bag! It&rsquo;s a great size and the zipper makes it perfect for a big carryall bag (especially for moms!) Under $50 &ndash; also ordered in tan!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Photo-Jun-07-6-57-19-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1813px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">It was so cute &ndash; he wanted to get a black backwards hat so he could match his dad on our trip. It&rsquo;s crazy because he looks so much like his dad here too. He&rsquo;s seriously his dad&rsquo;s little twin.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Photo-Jun-07-6-59-16-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1813px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">Never ceases to make me laugh. Love this kid.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"summer crocs\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Photo-Jun-07-7-29-45-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1813px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Guysssss who else is on the Croc train? I love them on Ollie and somehow ended up trying them on at Nordstrom and kind of love them. Tried them on in this pretty blush, lilac, and pink/orange color and they are all so pretty! I went home with two colors. (Can you guess which?)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"summer dresses\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Photo-Jun-07-4-57-14-PM-1.jpg\" style=\"height:1813px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Wanted to share a closer look at this dress&nbsp;in better lighting &ndash; it has the prettiest texture on the material and love the silhouette. Would also make a great cover up!</p>\r\n', 0, 'XX, Christine', '2021-06-25 18:53:46', 1, 0),
(11, 71, 'if-i-could-only-own-1-workout-sneaker--this-would-be-it.jpeg', '88', 'If I Could Only Own 1 Workout Sneaker, This Would Be It', '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"workout sneaker\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Instaoption2.jpg\" style=\"height:1700px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Photo-Sep-15-9-29-12-AM.jpg\" style=\"height:1700px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"adidas UltraBOOSTs\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Photo-Sep-15-2-46-13-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1939px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"adidas streetstyle\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Photo-Sep-15-9-25-29-AM.jpg\" style=\"height:1700px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The comfiest sneaks! I have in multiple colors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"adidas sneakers\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Photo-Sep-15-2-44-07-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1939px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"kids adidas outfit\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Photo-Sep-15-2-49-03-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1941px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How is he going to be one sooo soon! I die over&nbsp;<a href=\"https://shopstyle.it/l/bmskm\" rel=\"nofollow\">his mini track suit</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"kids in adidas\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Photo-Sep-15-2-47-19-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1941px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"adidas kids style\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Photo-Sep-15-9-34-32-AM.jpg\" style=\"height:1700px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"beckam andrew\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Photo-Sep-15-2-53-03-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1940px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"adidas workout sneaker\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Photo-Sep-15-2-55-00-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1978px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Beckam always wants to do everything Cody does. So adventurous!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"family adidas style\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Photo-Sep-15-2-26-10-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:2049px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"mens workout sneaker\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Photo-Sep-15-2-23-27-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:2049px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"family sportswear style and workout sneaker\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Photo-Sep-15-2-35-06-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:901px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"kids goofy adidas sweatshirt\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Photo-Sep-15-2-52-44-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1941px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"best workout sneakers\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Photo-Sep-15-2-35-19-PM.jpg\" style=\"height:1901px; width:1228px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"andrew family in adidas\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Photo-Sep-15-2-35-17-PM-1.jpg\" style=\"height:1939px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"toddler in adidas\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Photo-Sep-15-9-37-14-AM.jpg\" style=\"height:1700px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"best workout sneaker\" src=\"https://www.hellofashionblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Photo-Sep-15-9-37-15-AM.jpg\" style=\"height:1700px; width:1360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Over the years my sneaker collection has gradually overtaken my heel collection. My favorite workout sneakers of all time are hands down every variation of my adidas UltraBOOSTs.. I have multiple pairs of the&nbsp;UltraBOOSTs,&nbsp;and the UltraBOOST Xs and wear them all on repeat. I just got this pair&nbsp;in white and wore them all over Park City this past weekend. They are really lightweight and have a boost cushioning for extra support so it feels like you&rsquo;re walking/running on air.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">I also ordered this sweat set&nbsp;from Finish Line &ndash; I love borrowing from the boys! Especially in loungewear and sweats, I&rsquo;m loving the oversized fit so I ordered a size medium in this sweatshirt&nbsp;and small in joggers. Also love the oversized hoodie&nbsp;over biker shorts! Below are some other pieces I ordered from Finish Line for the family. You can also see more of our family adidas looks in this post.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 0, 'XX, Christine', '2021-06-25 18:53:16', 35, 2);
